==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spinozism
<hw>Spi*no"zism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The form of
Pantheism taught by Benedict <xex>Spinoza</xex>, that there is but one
substance, or infinite essence, in the universe, of which the so-called
material and spiritual beings and phenomena are only modes, and that one
this one substance is God.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>Spinosism</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spinozist</ent>⟦br⟧
